The paper deals with disentangling the representations of relevant attributes of data using Variational Autoencoders. This is a problem that is commonly addressed in the fields of machine learning and computer vision, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to one of the sub-categories in these fields. Specifically, the paper deals with image datasets, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of computer vision (cs.CV) or machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses an adversarial approach to minimize mutual information, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL).
